<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									DRUG ABUSE SCREENING TEST (DAST)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
last updated:  02-21-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-21-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements the Drug Abuse Screening Test (DAST) published by 

Skinner, H.A. (1982). The drug abuse screening test. Addictive Behaviors, 7, 363–371.

The DAST provides an way to screen for drug abuse using 28 self-report "yes/no" questions.

A paper and pencil version can be downloaded from:
www.drtepp.com/pdf/substance_abuse.pdf

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
TASK DESCRIPTION	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
28 yes-no questions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'dast.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								scale: 0 = no; 1 = yes
								R = automatically reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time in ms the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'dast_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version: 						Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
									
totalscore:							calculates the total score as the sum of all individual answers 
									(abuse affirmative = 1; other = 0)
									Range: 0 - 28


</usermanual>

**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
raw data
********************
DAST.iqdat

********************
summary data
********************
<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, 
expressions.totalscore)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
totalscore:							calculates the total score

<expressions>

/totalscore = radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2.response + radiobuttons.q3.response +
radiobuttons.q4R.response + radiobuttons.q5R.response + radiobuttons.q6.response + radiobuttons.q7R.response +
radiobuttons.q8.response + radiobuttons.q9.response + radiobuttons.q10.response + radiobuttons.q11.response +
radiobuttons.q12.response + radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14.response + radiobuttons.q15.response +
radiobuttons.q16.response + radiobuttons.q17.response + radiobuttons.q18.response + radiobuttons.q19.response +
radiobuttons.q20.response + radiobuttons.q21.response + radiobuttons.q22.response + radiobuttons.q23.response +
radiobuttons.q24.response + radiobuttons.q25.response + radiobuttons.q26.response + radiobuttons.q27.response +
radiobuttons.q28.response
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
NOTE: as a default all questions require a response to move on, to change this 
go to QUESTIONS and set all /required = true to /required = false

<caption instructions>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response." 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, true, false, false, 5, 1)
</caption>


<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. Have you used drugs other than those required for medical reasons?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. Have you abused prescription drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "3. Do you abuse more than one drug at a time?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4R>
/caption = "4. Can you get through the week without using drugs (other than those required for medical reasons)?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5R>
/caption = "5. Are you always able to stop using drugs when you want to?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. Do you abuse drugs on a continuous basis?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7R>
/caption = "7. Do you try to limit your drug use to certain situations?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "8. Have you had “blackouts” or “flashbacks” as a result of drug use?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9>
/caption = "9. Do you ever feel bad about your drug abuse?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. Does your spouse (or parents) ever complain about your involvement with drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11>
/caption = "11. Do your friends or relatives know or suspect you abuse drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12>
/caption = "12. Has drug abuse ever created problems between you and your spouse?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "13. Has any family member ever sought help for problems related to your drug use?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14>
/caption = "14. Have you ever lost friends because of your use of drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15>
/caption = "15. Have you ever neglected your family or missed work because of your use of drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16>
/caption = "16. Have you ever been in trouble at work because of drug abuse?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17>
/caption = "17. Have you ever lost a job because of drug abuse?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18>
/caption = "18. Have you gotten into fights when under the influence of drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q19>
/caption = "19. Have you ever been arrested because of unusual behavior while under the influence of drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q20>
/caption = "20. Have you ever been arrested for driving while under the influence of drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q21>
/caption = "21. Have you engaged in illegal activities in order to obtain drug?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q22>
/caption = "22. Have you ever been arrested for possession of illegal drugs?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q23>
/caption = "23. Have you ever experienced withdrawal symptoms as a result of heavy drug intake?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q24>
/caption = "24. Have you had medical problems as a result of your drug use (e.g., memory loss, hepatitis, convulsions, bleeding, etc.)?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q25>
/caption = "25. Have you ever gone to anyone for help for a drug problem?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q26>
/caption = "26. Have you ever been in a hospital for medical problems related to your drug use?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q27>
/caption = "27. Have you ever been involved in a treatment program specifically related to drug use?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q28>
/caption = "28. Have you been treated as an outpatient for problems related to drug abuse?"
/ options = ("Yes", "No")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/orientation = vertical
/required = true
</radiobuttons>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage DAST1>
/ caption = "The following questions concern information about your involvement and abuse of drugs.
"
/subcaption = "Drug abuse refers to 
(1) the use of prescribed or “over the counter” drugs in excess of the directions and 
(2) any non-medical use of drugs. 
" 
/ questions = [1 = instructions, q1, q2, q3]
</surveypage>


<surveypage DAST2>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q4R, q5R, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST3>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q7R, q8, q9]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST4>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 =  q10, q11, q12]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST5>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q13, q14, q15]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST6>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q16, q17, q18]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST7>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q19, q20, q21]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST8>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q22, q23, q24]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST9>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q25, q26, q27]
</surveypage>

<surveypage DAST10>
/ caption = "Carefully read each statement and decide whether your answer is yes or no. Then select the appropriate response.
" 
/ questions = [1 = q28]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<survey DAST>
/ pages = [
	1 = DAST1; 
	2 = DAST2; 
	3 = DAST3; 
	4 = DAST4; 
	5 = DAST5; 
	6 = DAST6;
	7 = DAST7;
	8 = DAST8;	
	9 = DAST9;
	10 = DAST10;
]
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, true, false, false, 5, 1)
/subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/showpagenumbers = false
/showquestionnumbers = false

/ backbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (80%, 90%)
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>


